    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I'm seeing a weird 500 error on our /api/v1/checkout/complete endpoint. It only happens intermittently, usually when there's high traffic. Here is a snippet from the logs during one of the crashes:\n\n[2023-10-27 14:22:01] ERROR: ConnectionTimeout during inventory_update_service call. \n[2023-10-27 14:22:01] ERROR: Failed to acquire lock on resource: db_transaction_lock_442.\n[2023-10-27 14:22:02] CRITICAL: Deadlock detected in transaction pool.\n[2023-10-27 14:22:02] FATAL: Internal Server Error - unexpected state in state_machine_v2.\n\nCan you look at this and tell me what's likely causing the instability?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The 500 error you're seeing is likely caused by a combination of high traffic leading to resource contention and a deadlock situation in your database. When the traffic spikes, your inventory update service might be trying to acquire a lock on the database resource, but due to the high number of requests, it can't get the lock in time, resulting in a connection timeout. This, in turn, leads to a deadlock situation in your transaction pool, which is causing the internal server error. To resolve this, you may need to optimize your database locking strategy and improve your application's ability to handle high traffic. Additionally, consider implementing a more robust error handling and retry mechanism to handle such situations gracefully.",
      "source": "target",
